  "firstAcquaintance": "A knight from the wanderers. Skilled in throwing techniques, she can nimbly use objects on the battlefield as her projectiles.",
  "personality": "Appears serious but is actually easy to get along with. Despite being poor, she never hesitates to share.",
  "like": "Weapons, pizza, sharing.",
  "familiarData": "Mier - the name sounds lovely, but she's a fierce fighter on the battlefield, feared by slave hunters. Mier is the spokesperson of the \"Wandering Knights\" faction among the wanderers, training fellow wanderers alongside her companions and forming patrol teams to fight against slave hunters.\nHer weapon is a sword, but she actually emulates knight lance techniques. When she throws her sword, it charges forward like a knight's charge, swiftly striking down enemies. With this martial skill, she inherited the name \"Don Quixote.\"\nThe wanderers' living conditions couldn't produce proper knights, so what Mier learned was more about chivalric spirit and combat techniques passed down through generations of wandering knights.\nMier loves to share. Even if she's starving, she wouldn't mind splitting her steamed bun in half for someone in need. Though she wears rags and survives by scavenging, she is, without a doubt, a great knight.\nMier likes to self-deprecatingly joke about being short, but that doesn't mean others can laugh at her height. She'll act like she doesn't care in the moment, but before long she'll find an excuse to punch them.",
